I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001307_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001307.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001307-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>",{"id":208,"html":209},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text after Kaibel in IG\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":211,"html":212},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Sacred to the spirits of the underworld. Klodia Balenteina, farewell. She lived 40 years. Ignatis Karikos made this for his own wife, for the sake of her memory.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":214,"html":215},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The text is distinctive for a number of features illustrating linguistic interference from Latin: the use of the Latin abbreviated header DMS (with interpuncts according to the transcriptions, not used in the rest of the text); the use of Latin numerals in line 3; the use of abbreviations both for \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἔζη(σεν) ἔ(τη)\u003C/span> and \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">μνή(μης) χάριν\u003C/span>. The unusual structure of the text (and use of χαῖρε which is not generally attested at Catania) further marks it out as distinctive, and Korhonen emphasises its extra-urban provenance.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":217,"html":218},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Ferrara 1829 387 no.4 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002005\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002005\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Franz 1853 5396 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">484\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Korhonen 2004 249 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001897\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001897\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":220,"html":221},"handnote"," Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    ",{"id":223,"html":224},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[226,228,231,232],{"html":227},"Text encoding: Jonathan Prag",{"id":229,"lang":96,"html":230},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"la\">D(is) · m(anibus) · s(acrum) ·\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Κλωδία Βαλεντεῖνα\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Κλωδία\">Κλωδία\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Βαλεντεῖνα\">Βαλεντεῖνα\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>χαῖρε ἔζη(σεν) ἔ(τη) \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"la\">XXXX\u003C/span>´ \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ἐποίησε ἰδίᾳ γυναι-\u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>κὶ \u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ἰγνᾶτις Κ